{
  "text": "One can check that \u039b is a Lagrangian submanifold of T * (B 3 \u00d7 B 3 ), see also [CITATION_1] . Thanks to our assumption, the manifold has no conjugate points. The Lagrangian \u039b away from the diagonal is the graph of the differential of the distance function i.e.",
  "correct_citation": {
